# Deploy-time config for menu's R2 + assets-DNS Tofu root. Copy to
# `infra/.env` (gitignored).
#
# The menu APPLICATION's deploy config (Hetzner VPS, container, secrets)
# lives at the repo-root `infra/` workspace — this file is only for the
# things this product owns: the R2 assets bucket and the
# assets.iedora.com custom-domain DNS record.
#
# All PRODUCTION SECRETS live in Bitwarden Secrets Manager — this file
# holds only non-secret config + the BWS access token that unlocks the
# vault. Lose the laptop → re-clone the repo, paste BWS_ACCESS_TOKEN back,
# you're back up.
#
# Filename does NOT match Next.js's auto-load pattern (.env, .env.local,
# .env.<env>) AND lives outside the project root, so `bun run dev` can't
# see any of this even if it walked the tree.

# ── Non-secret IDs (visible in DNS records anyway) ───────────────────────────

# Cloudflare account ID — dashboard → right sidebar. The zone ID is looked
# up automatically from PUBLIC_HOSTNAME below, no need to specify it here.
CLOUDFLARE_ACCOUNT_ID=

# Public hostname (must be a subdomain of a Cloudflare-managed zone in the
# account above). Used to derive the zone (everything after the first dot),
# the default assets hostname (`assets.<zone>`), and the CORS allowed origin
# on the R2 bucket. The DNS record / TLS for this hostname itself is NOT
# managed here — it's an A record to the Hetzner VPS managed at
# `infra/tofu/` at the repo root.
PUBLIC_HOSTNAME=menu.example.com

# GitHub Container Registry — your GH username; menu's image is built by
# the menu.yml CI workflow and pushed to ghcr.io/$GHCR_USER/menu.
GHCR_USER=

# ── Bitwarden Secrets Manager ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The ONE secret on disk. Generate via:
#   1. vault.bitwarden.com/#/sm → create project "iedora-deploy" → copy project UUID
#   2. Machine accounts → New → name "iedora-deploy" → add project with R/W
#   3. Access tokens → New → no expiry → copy the `0.xxx...` value
#
# Everything else (CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN, STATE_PASSPHRASE, …) lives in BWS.
# See docs/secrets.md.
BWS_ACCESS_TOKEN=
BWS_PROJECT_ID=
